<sect2 id="file-tim-export">
  <title>Export Image as Playstation TIM</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Export Image as TIM</primary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Formats</primary>
    <secondary>tim</secondary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect3>
    <title>Overview</title>

<!--
    Always crashing for me so a screenshot will have to wait.
    <figure>
      <title>The Playstation TIM Export dialog</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata format="PNG"
            fileref="images/dialogs/export-tim-dialog.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
-->
    <para>
      The Playstation TIM file format is a standard image file format for the
      Sony Playstation.
      It supports 4- and 8-bit indexed images, as well as 15- and 24-bit full
      color images.
    </para>
  </sect3>

  <sect3>
    <title>Options</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Type</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Select the type of TIM texture to export. Choices are:
          </para>
          <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>4BPP (Indexed)</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  Export as 4-bits (16 colors) indexed image.
                </para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>8BPP (Indexed)</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  Export as 8-bits (256 colors) indexed image.
                </para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>16BPP (RGB)</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  Export as 16-bits RGB color image.
                </para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>24BPP (RGB)</term>
              <listitem>
                <para>
                  Export as 24-bits RGB image.
                </para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Image X</term>
        <term>Image Y</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The origin X and Y coordinates of the image.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Palette X</term>
        <term>Palette Y</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The palette X and Y coordinates. Only used when one of the indexed
            formats is chosen.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </sect3>

</sect2>
